parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description:
The client token that is used to ensure the idempotence of the request.

You can use the client to generate the token, but you must make sure that the token is unique among different requests. The token can contain only ASCII characters and cannot exceed 64 characters in length.

parameters.name: QosId
parameters.description: The ID of the QoS policy.

parameters.name: QueueId
parameters.description: The ID of the QoS queue.

parameters.name: RegionId
parameters.description:
The region ID of the QoS policy.

You can call the [DescribeRegions](~~36063~~) operation to query the most recent region list.

parameters.name: RuleId
parameters.description: The ID of the QoS rule.
